         "html_value": "<p><hr /></p><p class=\"topdesc\"><i>In addition to using the name America, we will also refer to the continent as <i>Abya Yala</i>, a term used by the indigenous peoples of the continent (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('160fb48c-1711-491e-a1aa-e1257e7889af'); return false;\">Porto-Gon√ßalves, Carlos Walter, <htdate0>, pp. 39-43</a>).</i></p><p><h3>Description</h3>We are all <i>Homo sapiens</i> (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('2119e27f-6337-4b83-a551-31deb737ee3d'); return false;\">Stringer, Chris, <htdate0></a>). By exploring our search for the earliest common ancestor with <i>Homo neanderthalensis</i> (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('2119e27f-6337-4b83-a551-31deb737ee3d'); return false;\">Stringer, Chris, <htdate1></a>), we can deepen our understanding of our species' family tree. While this may seem like a simplification, it clearly demonstrates our shared humanity.</p><p>Animal evolution unfolds over vast stretches of time, punctuated by occasional bursts of rapid change (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('c6bc83e7-103d-44ea-8623-bafa1862860c'); return false;\">Sperling, Erik A., et Richard G. Stockey, <htdate2>, pp. 605-622</a>). In contrast, the evolution of language progresses swiftly (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('f49430b6-ab85-4d19-8d2b-d0ce06126dc4'); return false;\">Fitch, W.T., <htdate3>, 3-33</a>). This rapid linguistic evolution enables us to categorize and label groups of people and events, inadvertently fostering the perception of differences among us.</p><p><b>The events can be updated or added at any time based on new research. <span id=\"family_common_sn\"></span></b></p>",
